1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:02,040
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:03,780
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,210 --> 00:00:06,540
(Episode 18)

4
00:00:06,610 --> 00:00:09,510
If there are no other witnesses,
Ms. Gong Ju Ah, please come in.

5
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:13,990
- Hold on. Give us five minutes.
- It's okay, Director.

6
00:00:14,490 --> 00:00:16,050
I'm going in.

7
00:00:24,930 --> 00:00:25,930
Hold on a second.

8
00:00:43,110 --> 00:00:46,050
Stepmother, what are you doing here?

9
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:52,960
You see, I'm not much of a writer,

10
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:55,130
so I figured it'd be better
to say it in person.

11
00:00:57,030 --> 00:00:59,200
Tell them the other person involved
is here.

12
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:02,300
- Yes, right this way.
- Okay.

13
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:03,700
Wait.

14
00:01:05,070 --> 00:01:06,070
Yes?

15
00:01:06,910 --> 00:01:08,740
Please put aside
any personal feelings...

16
00:01:10,010 --> 00:01:12,480
and just state the facts.

17
00:01:12,980 --> 00:01:14,250
That's all I ask.

18
00:01:28,490 --> 00:01:30,430
What on earth is she thinking,
coming here?

19
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:34,070
Okay, listen.

20
00:01:34,630 --> 00:01:36,940
Call me the second you hear
about the results.

21
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:38,470
Everyone's worried.

22
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,240
Okay.

23
00:01:41,170 --> 00:01:43,640
Wait, what's Bucket's wife
doing there?

24
00:01:44,110 --> 00:01:46,680
I have a really bad feeling
she's not going to defend her.

25
00:01:47,110 --> 00:01:50,420
See? You should've just agreed
to do "Human Theater."

26
00:01:50,620 --> 00:01:53,120
Then she'd be grateful enough
to put in a good word for her.

27
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:56,050
Hey, I only just heard about it
this morning myself.

28
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:58,120
Maybe we should go beg her
for help now?

29
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:00,460
Hey, stop making such a fuss...

30
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:02,160
and wait patiently.

31
00:02:02,430 --> 00:02:03,530
I can't help it. I'm so anxious.

32
00:02:04,030 --> 00:02:08,670
I ran into Dong Suk the other day,
and she was asking...

33
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:09,900
if you messed up that shot
on purpose...

34
00:02:09,970 --> 00:02:12,470
and suggesting that
Ju Ah pushed her on purpose too.

35
00:02:12,970 --> 00:02:16,040
For crying out loud.
This is driving me nuts.

36
00:02:16,810 --> 00:02:17,810
Darn it.

37
00:02:17,940 --> 00:02:20,250
(Disciplinary Committee)

38
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:22,950
(Taehan Group)

39
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:26,380
Ms. Gong Ju Ah, you may go in.

40
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:28,220
Yes.

41
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:36,690
Thank you for coming.

42
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:38,830
Not at all.

43
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,670
I'll walk you to your car.

44
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:43,640
No, you're busy.
It's fine. I'll see myself out.

45
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,240
Bye, then.

46
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:55,710
How did it go?
What did your mother say?

47
00:02:58,650 --> 00:03:00,020
She put in a good word for her.

48
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,450
What exactly did she say?

49
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:07,930
Could you describe your injuries
at the time of the incident?

50
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:14,130
According to the medical report,
the physical injury was very minor,

51
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,830
but the emotional trauma
was significant.

52
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:21,670
You felt the incident with
Ms. Gong Ju Ah was deliberate,

53
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:24,340
which in turn caused
this emotional trauma.

54
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:25,780
Is that correct?

55
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:31,720
The trauma I experienced...

56
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:34,150
was not because of Ms. Gong.

57
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:36,450
It was because of
the way the company...

58
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:38,720
chose to handle this incident.

59
00:03:39,690 --> 00:03:42,890
For a major corporation to punish
an employee for something so minor,

60
00:03:43,330 --> 00:03:46,060
rather than protect them?

61
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:50,470
It makes no sense to me whatsoever.

62
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,700
The core issue of this case
is whether...

63
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:56,470
- Ms. Gong acted deliberately.
- Deliberate?

64
00:03:58,410 --> 00:04:01,880
I consider Ms. Gong Ju Ah my savior.

65
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:07,190
If not for her, my eye, or my nose,

66
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:10,760
or my cheekbone could have been
seriously damaged, don't you think?

67
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,320
I'm the one who got hurt,

68
00:04:13,660 --> 00:04:18,500
and I've made my position clear.
If Ms. Gong is penalized in any way,

69
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:21,130
I'll report
on my social media accounts...

70
00:04:21,130 --> 00:04:23,470
that my testimony was ignored...

71
00:04:23,670 --> 00:04:26,870
to make an employee a scapegoat.

72
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:29,410
(Chair of
the Disciplinary Committee)

73
00:04:36,980 --> 00:04:38,320
Wow. She doesn't pull any punches.

74
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:42,990
I have a good feeling about this.
Try not to worry, Doctor.

75
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:46,120
Honestly,
that was not what I expected.

76
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,230
So I'm a little flustered.

77
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:17,820
(Taehan Group)

78
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:22,030
So, what happened?

79
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:27,400
They ruled
that it wasn't intentional.

80
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,730
They told me
to get right back to work.

81
00:05:33,910 --> 00:05:37,410
Quite the dramatic entrance
for a dramatic result,

82
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:38,980
all thanks to
our Director Yang's mother.

83
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:48,390
Yes. Really?

84
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:55,430
What? What did she say?
Is Ju Ah okay?

85
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,760
Yes. Okay, got it.

86
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:01,300
What did she say?
Did she defend her?

87
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:05,500
Yes. She apparently told them
that if they punished Ju Ah,

88
00:06:06,070 --> 00:06:08,540
she wouldn't let it slide.

89
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:13,540
What's gotten into her?
I thought she'd demand punishment.

90
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:21,790
What? Come on,
you were all thinking it.

91
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,460
- You're not wrong.
- She's not wrong.

92
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:28,160
No, I wasn't thinking that.

93
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:32,660
- Come on.
- Mom, what does that make us, then?

94
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,930
Exactly. Come on, Mom.

95
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,140
But still...

96
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,840
I know everyone was
on pins and needles,

97
00:06:41,870 --> 00:06:43,940
so I'm relieved this was resolved
without disciplinary action.

98
00:06:44,610 --> 00:06:48,610
Director Yang's mother
spoke up forcefully for me,

99
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:53,950
and our Design Team's petition
was also a huge help.

100
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:58,920
She's back, and she's okay.
Don't cry.

101
00:07:01,930 --> 00:07:04,500
Excuse me, Director.
About the video of your mother...

102
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,430
You know it's turned
into a viral challenge, right?

103
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:09,970
Yes. I'll take care of it,
so don't worry.

104
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,740
We're counting on you, Director.

105
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,740
After these recent incidents,

106
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:18,740
I'm sure you can all feel
that our division is a target.

107
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:22,450
It feels like they're trying to turn
each slip-up into a big deal, right?

108
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:25,920
Don't let this shake you.

109
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:31,320
Director Yang and I will protect
the Fashion Division at all costs.

110
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:32,790
Got it?

111
00:07:34,460 --> 00:07:35,660
Let's go.

112
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:36,730
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

113
00:07:37,230 --> 00:07:38,230
Let's go.

114
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:58,250
Who wears something like that
to the market?

115
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:00,790
Wait, isn't that the woman
from the Korean Medicine clinic?

116
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,590
Yes, you're right.

117
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:06,660
I thought she'd be too embarrassed
to even leave the house,

118
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:09,760
but look at her, parading in public.
Unbelievable.

119
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:20,810
I didn't do anything wrong.
Why should I stay cooped up at home?

120
00:08:21,010 --> 00:08:23,510
Besides, you got a kick out of it,
didn't you?

121
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:26,940
It was pretty funny.
How can someone...

122
00:08:27,210 --> 00:08:29,480
tumble around like that?

123
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:35,050
I'm so glad I could provide
some entertainment for you all.

124
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:38,190
But seriously,

125
00:08:38,260 --> 00:08:40,690
did Dr. Gong's daughter...

126
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:44,330
- push you on purpose?
- Goodness!

127
00:08:45,230 --> 00:08:48,370
- Of course not. It was an accident.
- Right.

128
00:08:48,370 --> 00:08:51,200
Dr. Gong's daughter tried
to keep me from getting hurt.

129
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:53,470
She used her own body
to break my fall.

130
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:57,480
You heard her.
Why are you still asking?

131
00:08:57,540 --> 00:09:02,010
You started the rumor,
so why are you blaming me?

132
00:09:03,050 --> 00:09:06,850
Stop spreading rumors like that.
All right?

133
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:09,050
All right, we get it.

134
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:10,590
Well, then.

135
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:18,630
- She really said that?
- Yes! "My goodness."

136
00:09:19,130 --> 00:09:22,070
"Of course not.
She didn't push me on purpose."

137
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:25,440
"Dr. Gong's daughter
used her body to break my fall."

138
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,570
That's exactly what she said!

139
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:29,640
Here she comes.

140
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:30,910
My goodness.

141
00:09:30,910 --> 00:09:31,980
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

142
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:32,980
Hello.

143
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:38,220
I heard what you did for Ju Ah.
Thank you.

144
00:09:39,950 --> 00:09:43,190
Not at all.
I only did what was right.

145
00:09:43,690 --> 00:09:46,320
So, how are you feeling?
Are you all right?

146
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:50,330
I'm fine, thanks. And thank you
for the medicine you sent over.

147
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:54,730
Let me know when you run out.
I can give you as much as you need.

148
00:09:56,130 --> 00:09:58,340
Thank you, ma'am.

149
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:01,140
Take care.

150
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:03,840
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

151
00:10:03,910 --> 00:10:05,940
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

152
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:17,150
Seriously,
a phone call would've been nice.

153
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,790
Oh, Se Ri!

154
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:24,960
So, what happened?
Did Jeong Han's daughter get fired?

155
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:28,430
Of course not.
I smoothed things over for her.

156
00:10:28,930 --> 00:10:32,970
- Really?
- Yes. It's all sorted out.

157
00:10:33,540 --> 00:10:36,310
That's fantastic.
That's my Se Ri. Well done.

158
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:40,950
But still,
you should've given me a heads-up.

159
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:44,080
If you just handle it like that,
we lose our leverage.

160
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:47,390
Oh, just trust me and wait, honey.

161
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:54,190
- What? It's Gong Jeong Han.
- Quick, answer it.

162
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:01,230
Hey, Jeong Han. What's up?

163
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:07,410
The samples with customer feedback
have gone into revision,

164
00:11:07,470 --> 00:11:09,970
and Hyegyeong wants us
to sign the retail contract...

165
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:13,940
Director?

166
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:15,310
Yes?

167
00:11:16,150 --> 00:11:19,920
What brilliant idea has you
so lost in thought this time?

168
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:26,590
About my stepmother's video.
The one people are imitating...

169
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:29,790
Oh, right.
Are people still doing that?

170
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,830
Yes. It's blowing up
all over the place.

171
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:36,500
Don't you think it'll just blow over
after a while?

172
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:40,670
Does it have to?
I was thinking we could use it.

173
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:47,040
But if you do, you must get
your stepmother's permission.

174
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:53,880
So, can I give you a ride home?

175
00:11:54,090 --> 00:11:55,120
What?

176
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:14,310
You two aren't about to fight,
are you?

177
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,440
Why would we fight?
Don't be ridiculous.

178
00:12:16,710 --> 00:12:19,080
Just get us some meat, okay?
Give us your bestseller.

179
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:20,640
Okay, you got it.

180
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:26,080
Shouldn't your son be studying?

181
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:30,290
- He's working?
- Oh, he wanted a break,

182
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,620
so I let him.

183
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:35,890
Do you want some?

184
00:12:36,230 --> 00:12:38,000
What? Oh, sure.

185
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:42,030
So?

186
00:12:42,670 --> 00:12:43,970
Why did you ask to meet?

187
00:12:45,070 --> 00:12:46,070
Got something to say?

188
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:57,380
I'm sorry.

189
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:02,450
Sorry? For what?

190
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:05,920
Honestly, at first...

191
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,530
That video of your wife
falling down...

192
00:13:09,190 --> 00:13:10,390
I thought
you posted it on purpose...

193
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,700
just to make me feel bad.

194
00:13:13,330 --> 00:13:15,830
Goodness. Come on, man.

195
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:19,840
You really think the worst of us,
don't you?

196
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:21,070
I do.

197
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:24,110
Yes. Well...
I guess I can't blame you.

198
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,910
I thought you were trying
to make me feel guilty...

199
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:30,410
so you could persuade me
to do "Human Theater" with you.

200
00:13:30,780 --> 00:13:32,420
Oh, come on.

201
00:13:32,820 --> 00:13:37,020
If that was my plan, I would've made
my demands once the video was up.

202
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,220
Exactly.

203
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:42,490
I guess this whole time,
I've really...

204
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:46,730
- completely misunderstood you.
- You think so?

205
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,670
Well, now that that's cleared up,

206
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,300
I should be thanking you.

207
00:13:51,270 --> 00:13:54,670
No, it's just...
I'm the one who's grateful.

208
00:13:58,110 --> 00:13:59,580
As you know,

209
00:14:00,410 --> 00:14:01,410
I...

210
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:03,180
treat other people better...

211
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,580
than I do my own family.

212
00:14:05,950 --> 00:14:09,720
- Right, you tend to do that.
- But that's because...

213
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:12,920
my family can fend for themselves
just fine. You know?

214
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:14,830
Take Ju Ah, for example.

215
00:14:15,130 --> 00:14:18,960
Like her mom, she's always been
sharp and independent as a kid.

216
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:23,170
So whenever I tried to do something
for her or give her a hand,

217
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:26,440
she'd say, "Dad, I've got this,"
every single time.

218
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:29,510
I mean, she wouldn't let me hold
her hand to keep her from falling.

219
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:31,780
She insisted she could do it all
by herself. You see?

220
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:35,810
But then, when she did fall,
she'd get right back up on her own,

221
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:39,220
dust herself off,
and just keep on walking.

222
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:44,050
She's never once cried
in front of me...

223
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:46,220
or told me
she was having a hard time.

224
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:48,530
For a kid like that...

225
00:14:48,890 --> 00:14:53,100
If I can't help her as her dad,
I shouldn't hold her back, right?

226
00:14:53,530 --> 00:14:57,270
She gave up so much she worked for
to do something she loves,

227
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:01,240
and to think she might get fired
because of me...

228
00:15:01,570 --> 00:15:03,270
I'm serious. All morning,

229
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,680
my hands just wouldn't stop shaking.

230
00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:08,410
I had no idea.

231
00:15:10,350 --> 00:15:12,320
Thank you. I really mean it.

232
00:15:12,950 --> 00:15:14,050
Forget about it, man.

233
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:17,550
You know,

234
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:20,460
when I backed out of doing
"Human Theater,"

235
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:23,560
you thought I was just sulking
over what you said, didn't you?

236
00:15:24,830 --> 00:15:26,460
Well, yes, something like that.

237
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:28,400
To be honest, back then,

238
00:15:29,130 --> 00:15:32,370
I was wondering
if we were even still friends.

239
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:34,640
Since it didn't feel sincere,

240
00:15:35,140 --> 00:15:37,240
the idea of doing a show
about friendship...

241
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,740
just didn't sit right with me.

242
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:43,110
Right.

243
00:15:44,420 --> 00:15:45,920
But today,

244
00:15:47,690 --> 00:15:49,390
I saw how sincere you were.

245
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:52,760
So, on Monday,

246
00:15:53,660 --> 00:15:55,630
let's sign the contract...

247
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:57,490
for "Human Theater."

248
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:01,670
My gosh, Jeong Han.

249
00:16:02,070 --> 00:16:03,830
We didn't help you
expecting anything in return.

250
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:05,640
So if you're not really
feeling up to it,

251
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:08,970
- you don't have to do it.
- No, now I want to do it.

252
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,740
- Really?
- Yes, of course.

253
00:16:14,210 --> 00:16:15,410
Man, thank you.

254
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:18,750
- Seriously, thank you.
- Come on. It's nothing.

255
00:16:20,050 --> 00:16:22,650
Hey, Dong Ik.
This time, for real, okay?

256
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:25,690
- Let's kill it. All right? Cheers!
- You got it.

257
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:28,660
You should eat something
with your drinks.

258
00:16:28,990 --> 00:16:29,990
It's bad to drink
on an empty stomach.

259
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:32,660
Will do. Thanks, handsome.

260
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:37,940
Hey, Woo Jae, you should see
how much meat Dr. Yang can eat.

261
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,570
Hey, you still eat like a horse,
don't you?

262
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,870
You bet.
A kilo of meat at once? Easy.

263
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:49,610
Hey, listen.
He grew up on Grandma's spicy pork,

264
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:52,850
- and that's how he grew so tall.
- Really?

265
00:16:53,150 --> 00:16:55,820
Yes, that's right. Back when
I was eating it all the time,

266
00:16:55,950 --> 00:16:57,920
I grew 10cm a year.

267
00:16:58,990 --> 00:17:02,090
Wow, Grandma's spicy pork recipe
really goes way back.

268
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:06,500
Woo Jae! What are you waiting for?
Go get some more meat and soju.

269
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:07,770
Okay.

270
00:17:07,770 --> 00:17:09,870
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

271
00:17:09,870 --> 00:17:10,870
Hey.

272
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:13,100
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

273
00:17:13,170 --> 00:17:17,010
- Man, how long has it been?
- Tell me about it.

274
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:19,910
It's been well over 30 years.

275
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:22,710
Where does the time go?

276
00:17:24,950 --> 00:17:25,980
Still,

277
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,820
being able to sit here
having a drink together again...

278
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:31,390
It's really nice. You know?

279
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:34,320
All right.

280
00:17:34,830 --> 00:17:35,830
Yes.

281
00:17:48,210 --> 00:17:51,210
My gosh!
Was that your stomach growling?

282
00:17:51,540 --> 00:17:54,280
I know, right? For a second,
I thought it was thunder.

283
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:58,680
No wonder.
You barely touched your sandwich.

284
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:00,550
Oh, no. Are you starving?

285
00:18:00,820 --> 00:18:04,860
- Should I find a place nearby?
- No, it's fine. I'll eat at home.

286
00:18:07,490 --> 00:18:09,030
I'm craving some Argentinian food.

287
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:11,760
Oh, that makes sense.

288
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,730
Since you lived there for so long,
you must miss a lot of the food.

289
00:18:15,630 --> 00:18:16,870
Funny, isn't it?

290
00:18:17,940 --> 00:18:20,670
Back then, all I ever craved
was Korean food.

291
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:26,110
I heard there's an Argentinian place
in Gonghyeon-dong.

292
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:27,810
Want to go together this weekend?

293
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:33,220
I'll have to check my schedule.
It's my grandma's birthday.

294
00:18:33,650 --> 00:18:34,650
Really?

295
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:39,260
I know your birthday.
I should note your grandma's too.

296
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:41,730
You remember my birthday?

297
00:18:41,860 --> 00:18:44,190
Of course.
It's the passcode for my place.

298
00:18:45,860 --> 00:18:47,030
My gosh.

299
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:52,140
So when's my birthday? Your turn.

300
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:58,580
- When was it again?
- What?

301
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:00,010
Oh, you're getting a call.

302
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:02,010
- Go ahead and answer it.
- Please.

303
00:19:02,550 --> 00:19:04,410
This phone call saved you,
Gong Ju Ah.

304
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,490
Yes, Dad.

305
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,950
- All right.
- Hey, this is the new trend.

306
00:19:11,020 --> 00:19:13,890
Puppy. Kitty.

307
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:16,790
- Heart, a heart.
- A cheek heart!

308
00:19:16,860 --> 00:19:19,630
- Let's do a kissy face!
- Cheek heart!

309
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:21,430
Let's make you look good!

310
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:23,900
He must be a really close friend
of your father's.

311
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,740
You know my friend
who came by the other day?

312
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:31,110
You mean that cute girl
who has a crush on you?

313
00:19:33,410 --> 00:19:34,710
That's her father.

314
00:19:37,850 --> 00:19:40,920
Now, I see the resemblance.
She takes after her father.

315
00:19:42,450 --> 00:19:43,450
You think so?

316
00:19:44,090 --> 00:19:45,090
Hey, Gong Woo Jae!

317
00:19:48,590 --> 00:19:49,860
You're so photogenic.

318
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:51,860
- This is...
- Isn't it romantic?

319
00:19:52,130 --> 00:19:54,830
- Wow, what a movie star.
- Hey, give me a little Photoshop.

320
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:58,470
- Looking sharp, Dong Ik!
- I look more dependable, don't I?

321
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:02,170
- This one isn't so bad.
- You two are so lovey-dovey today.

322
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,340
- What?
- What?

323
00:20:03,540 --> 00:20:06,010
Son!
Hey, you know who this is, right?

324
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:08,810
- My handsome son.
- Yes. Of course, I know him!

325
00:20:09,180 --> 00:20:13,050
Our Director Yang
of the great Taehan Group!

326
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:15,290
Dad, how drunk are you?

327
00:20:15,390 --> 00:20:18,590
Hey, sweetheart!
My daughter, come here.

328
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:20,620
Hey, get away from me!

329
00:20:21,460 --> 00:20:24,330
Hey, see? Right?
She always tells me to go away.

330
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:25,400
I was right, wasn't I?

331
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:30,700
Hey, sweetie.

332
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:35,270
- Why aren't you having any meat?
- I already had dinner.

333
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:39,440
Come on, this one's on me. Here...

334
00:20:39,740 --> 00:20:44,280
Hey, it's delicious. Have a bite.
Come on! It's really good.

335
00:20:48,150 --> 00:20:50,020
- It's actually really good.
- Really?

336
00:20:50,020 --> 00:20:51,460
- Yes.
- We should order more then.

337
00:20:52,390 --> 00:20:56,060
- Order more! Order a lot!
- But I'm supposed to be on a diet.

338
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:00,430
What are you talking about?
You're beautiful.

339
00:21:00,430 --> 00:21:01,500
Don't lose any weight.

340
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:03,770
<i>That's just life</i>

341
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:05,700
Hey!

342
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,140
Hold on.

343
00:21:08,970 --> 00:21:10,070
Wait, you two...

344
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:14,540
You kids get along now, you hear?

345
00:21:15,650 --> 00:21:16,650
That's right, you two.

346
00:21:17,410 --> 00:21:18,820
Just get along already!

347
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:20,920
Of course, we will.

348
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:23,690
I had a crush on Ju Ah
before I went to study abroad.

349
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,620
Come on. Why are you bringing up
ancient history?

350
00:21:26,690 --> 00:21:30,260
Oh, no! Looks like our Director Yang
was a step too late.

351
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:35,170
My daughter already has a boyfriend.
Should I tell her to dump him?

352
00:21:35,370 --> 00:21:37,870
- You want to break up with him?
- At a time like this, I...

353
00:21:38,540 --> 00:21:40,240
want to tell you an old story.

354
00:21:40,570 --> 00:21:45,080
Once upon a time,
our Jeong Han was very popular.

355
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:48,350
You know why?
At the school festival,

356
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:49,510
he'd bring his acoustic guitar...

357
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:51,950
and sing like a total pro.

358
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,380
- You remember that, right?
- Yes. That's right.

359
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:59,020
Hey, I even had a fan club,
didn't I?

360
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:01,890
What was it called again?

361
00:22:03,130 --> 00:22:04,700
- Gongjeongdan!
- Gongjeongdan!

362
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,530
And for the little brother...
Gongjindan.

363
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,770
<i>I'm on top of the world</i>

364
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,840
<i>With the one who loves me</i>

365
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:17,570
<i>With my Jeong Han</i>

366
00:22:17,740 --> 00:22:21,910
<i>- I want to walk my own path</i>
<i>- I really do</i>

367
00:22:21,980 --> 00:22:25,420
<i>I have been so lonely</i>
<i>and had such a hard time</i>

368
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:30,450
- I was so lonely.
- Hey, they stole our song, right?

369
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:33,360
Let's let them have it tonight.
They look so happy.

370
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:35,090
Don't you ever leave me again.

371
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:36,960
They get along so well.

372
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:40,130
It's a shame they wasted
so much time as enemies, right?

373
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:43,100
Well, at least
they're getting along now.

374
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,740
Hey, what are you doing?
What if they see?

375
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:49,110
Who cares?
They're too drunk to even remember.

376
00:22:49,710 --> 00:22:50,740
Yang Hyun Bin!

377
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:53,240
Yes, Father.

378
00:22:53,510 --> 00:22:56,310
For round two. Let's go!
Everyone, follow me!

379
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:59,220
Round two at my place!

380
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:00,880
What? All right.

381
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:03,190
- We're really doing this?
- We're doing this.

382
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:06,090
- Let's go!
- Let's do it!

383
00:23:06,090 --> 00:23:09,430
I was wondering who was making
all that noise. It's you, doctors.

384
00:23:10,190 --> 00:23:11,830
- Oh, the cops.
- It's the cops!

385
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:14,630
Jeong Han, run!
They're here for you.

386
00:23:15,170 --> 00:23:18,940
- The crime? Stealing my heart!
- What? I'm busted.

387
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:22,470
I'm so sorry, Officer.
This is my first offense,

388
00:23:22,610 --> 00:23:25,210
so I beg for your leniency.

389
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:28,680
Yes, we'll be lenient with you. Yes.

390
00:23:28,980 --> 00:23:31,850
Dad, stop it! I'm sorry.

391
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:34,850
- We'll get them home.
- All right. Get home safe.

392
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:35,920
You have confessed to your crime.

393
00:23:36,090 --> 00:23:37,950
- Yes!
- As punishment for your crime,

394
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:40,160
I sentence you to a piggyback ride!

395
00:23:40,620 --> 00:23:42,060
Father! Good grief.

396
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:46,060
<i>The crime of stealing my heart</i>

397
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:50,400
<i>You are a thief of love</i>

398
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:52,340
Wow. That's...

399
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:53,870
It's nice to see.

400
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:55,710
It's the first time I've seen them
like this since I've been here.

401
00:23:55,770 --> 00:23:57,270
It's such a relief.

402
00:23:57,770 --> 00:24:00,940
I was worried Dr. Yang's wife
was going to make a big scene.

403
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:03,810
Gosh, tell me about it.
I thought it'd get out of hand,

404
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:07,020
- but it seems they worked it out.
- I know, right? It's great to see.

405
00:24:08,550 --> 00:24:11,890
Good grief. How much did he drink?

406
00:24:12,220 --> 00:24:16,390
A ton. They were so loud that
the police actually showed up.

407
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:21,700
Dong Ik. Let's go for round 2.
Round 2! Dong Ik...

408
00:24:21,770 --> 00:24:23,170
Look at him. Just look at him.

409
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,600
Looks like they had a good time.

410
00:24:26,170 --> 00:24:30,910
Dong Ik... My Dong Ik, my buddy...

411
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:35,710
Dong Ik...

412
00:24:36,650 --> 00:24:39,180
<i>My Se Ri, from outer space</i>

413
00:24:39,250 --> 00:24:41,650
Once upon a time,
Se Ri came looking for Dong Ik.

414
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:43,290
Hey, where's my Se Ri?

415
00:24:43,390 --> 00:24:44,390
There's Se Ri!

416
00:24:44,750 --> 00:24:46,490
- You're not Se Ri?
- Oh, brother, honestly!

417
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,820
There's my beautiful Se Ri!

418
00:24:48,390 --> 00:24:49,490
He's really drunk.

419
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:50,930
Honestly,
why did you call Hyun Bin...

420
00:24:50,930 --> 00:24:52,630
and drag him out there?
He must be exhausted.

421
00:24:52,630 --> 00:24:56,170
Not at all.
I'm actually in a great mood today.

422
00:24:56,330 --> 00:24:58,000
- Let's get you inside, Father.
- Hold on a minute.

423
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:01,610
Dong Suk, do you have any idea
what your big brother did today?

424
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:04,610
So you made up with Dr. Gong.
I heard everything.

425
00:25:04,710 --> 00:25:07,740
And you know who I have to thank?
Your sister-in-law.

426
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:11,180
Cha Se Ri is a genius.
A real genius.

427
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:15,490
Honey! You're very drunk.
Let's get you inside to bed, okay?

428
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:19,990
How on earth did she use that video
to get us to make up?

429
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:21,060
A few words for the press, please!

430
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:22,930
Hyun Bin!
Let's get him inside quickly.

431
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:25,030
- Father! That's enough. Come on.
- Get inside. Hurry.

432
00:25:25,330 --> 00:25:28,430
Wow, my gosh.
I never would've imagined that.

433
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:32,100
<i>Cha Se Ri is the absolute best</i>

434
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:35,240
- I'll be a superstar on TV!
- Get inside!

435
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:38,710
How do you do?
I'm Yang Dong Ik, not Bucket.

436
00:25:39,110 --> 00:25:41,810
Sure, whatever. Go ahead
and become a global superstar.

437
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,880
- I'm going to head in.
- Okay.

438
00:25:45,220 --> 00:25:47,820
I swear...
What am I going to do with him?

439
00:25:54,090 --> 00:25:55,130
Here, let me get that.

440
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:58,330
Dad passed out
the second he hit the pillow.

441
00:25:59,860 --> 00:26:03,970
I'm surprised he even called you.
Were you at home when he called?

442
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:07,270
No, I was actually on my way down
to see you.

443
00:26:07,370 --> 00:26:08,610
Me? To see me?

444
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:13,040
You left before
I could even thank you properly.

445
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:15,210
Oh, please. It was nothing.

446
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:19,550
You thought Ju Ah pushed you
intentionally, didn't you?

447
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:23,290
The thought did cross my mind
that she might have.

448
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:27,390
I'm really grateful
you didn't say that out loud.

449
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:31,590
I did well, right?
Our families made up because of it.

450
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:33,460
And look how happy your dad is.

451
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:36,770
But it was so embarrassing for you.
Are you okay after that?

452
00:26:36,770 --> 00:26:38,800
That video's still going around.

453
00:26:39,770 --> 00:26:43,410
It all turned out for the best,
so I think I'm fine.

454
00:26:43,770 --> 00:26:46,280
Besides, I love the attention.

455
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:48,580
- You know I do.
- In that case,

456
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:50,910
could we take it a step further?

457
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:55,490
We could spin this negative press
into PR.

458
00:26:56,190 --> 00:26:59,120
My goodness.
You got an idea from all this?

459
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,930
A world-class expert really is
on another level.

460
00:27:09,670 --> 00:27:10,900
How are you feeling?

461
00:27:11,900 --> 00:27:14,970
And of all times, we're all out
of bean sprouts and everything.

462
00:27:15,170 --> 00:27:18,510
I'm fine.
Just get me a hangover drink later.

463
00:27:19,810 --> 00:27:21,280
Here, drink this. Honey water.

464
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:22,880
- What?
- My goodness.

465
00:27:24,180 --> 00:27:28,120
My own daughter is caring for me...
Wow, I feel better already.

466
00:27:28,220 --> 00:27:29,220
Thanks, honey.

467
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:33,020
Mother, even in his sleep,

468
00:27:33,090 --> 00:27:34,760
he was calling out for Dong Ik.
Did you know that?

469
00:27:35,330 --> 00:27:38,400
When he was a kid,
he was always talking about Dong Ik.

470
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:40,730
They were practically
joined at the hip.

471
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:44,370
Yesterday, it felt like a reunion
for a family separated at birth.

472
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:45,600
You little punk.

473
00:27:46,770 --> 00:27:48,000
Hey, Jeong Han...

474
00:27:48,670 --> 00:27:50,310
You should've brought me along.

475
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:54,380
Hey, the big brothers
had things to discuss.

476
00:27:55,850 --> 00:27:59,250
Oh, you all know Grandma's birthday
is this Sunday, right?

477
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,550
- Yes, we know.
- Of course. We know.

478
00:28:01,550 --> 00:28:05,420
I was going to book a table for 5 p.m.
at our usual Korean restaurant.

479
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,720
- Woo Jae, are you free?
- Yes, I'm good.

480
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:10,930
The owner hasn't been well,
so he put the place up for sale.

481
00:28:11,130 --> 00:28:13,660
He said they're closed
on weekends until it sells.

482
00:28:13,860 --> 00:28:17,630
- Really? They put it up for sale?
- Yes.

483
00:28:17,700 --> 00:28:22,670
Ju Ah. About that reservation...
Is it possible to cancel it?

484
00:28:23,540 --> 00:28:25,410
Why, Grandma?
Do you want to go somewhere else?

485
00:28:25,710 --> 00:28:29,350
No, it's... I was just...

486
00:28:29,650 --> 00:28:31,780
I've had this on my mind.

487
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:36,050
What do you think
about inviting Dr. Yang...

488
00:28:36,850 --> 00:28:39,260
and his family over
for a meal this Sunday?

489
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:42,260
Mom. Are you serious?

490
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:43,560
I am.

491
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:46,460
I just feel strongly
that it's what I want to do.

492
00:28:47,300 --> 00:28:51,130
- What does everyone else think?
- That's a great idea.

493
00:28:51,630 --> 00:28:54,170
Hey, are you okay with that?

494
00:28:54,370 --> 00:28:57,310
Yes. Of course.
You two are good with it, right?

495
00:28:57,370 --> 00:28:59,810
- Yes, we're fine.
- I like it. It's a great idea.

496
00:29:00,540 --> 00:29:01,780
But what about you, Mom?

497
00:29:03,150 --> 00:29:07,350
I'm still not a fan of that woman,
and it feels awkward, but...

498
00:29:08,850 --> 00:29:10,520
since this is what Mother wants,

499
00:29:10,990 --> 00:29:14,320
I'm willing to change my mind
and try to get along.

500
00:29:15,630 --> 00:29:18,360
Thank you. I appreciate
you understanding how I feel.

501
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,460
Wow, Mom, that's huge progress.

502
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:23,000
You must be grateful
she helped Ju Ah.

503
00:29:23,070 --> 00:29:24,100
She was.

504
00:29:24,730 --> 00:29:27,640
I mean, I have the time, but...

505
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:30,010
I just don't know
how to do anything to help.

506
00:29:30,270 --> 00:29:32,580
Don't you worry. You've got me.

507
00:29:32,940 --> 00:29:34,810
Mom, I'll help too. Don't worry.

508
00:29:34,810 --> 00:29:37,850
- That's the spirit.
- I'll just make the seaweed soup.

509
00:29:38,350 --> 00:29:39,920
I'm not confident
I can make anything else.

510
00:29:40,450 --> 00:29:42,150
And you're confident
with the seaweed soup?

511
00:29:42,450 --> 00:29:43,720
Quiet, you.

512
00:29:45,490 --> 00:29:48,160
Okay, I'll give their family a call.

513
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:53,100
- Don't tell them it's my birthday.
- Of course, we won't.

514
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:55,100
Good.

515
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:56,970
Her seaweed soup...
That's a risky move.

516
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:00,040
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

517
00:30:00,100 --> 00:30:02,270
Gong Jeong Han from
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic!

518
00:30:02,740 --> 00:30:04,710
Yang Dong Ik
from Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic!

519
00:30:05,380 --> 00:30:07,810
Hey, try these hangover pills.
It'll sort you right out.

520
00:30:07,880 --> 00:30:12,420
Thanks!
Hey, have this milk thistle drink!

521
00:30:12,580 --> 00:30:13,580
For me? This is the good stuff.

522
00:30:14,220 --> 00:30:15,950
- Let's drink up!
- Yes, let's.

523
00:30:16,150 --> 00:30:17,150
All right.

524
00:30:18,150 --> 00:30:21,620
<i>Cheers, and down it goes!</i>

525
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:29,730
- Hey! That really hits the spot!
- To your liver's health!

526
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:31,470
- This is nice.
- I'll take that. Give it here.

527
00:30:31,530 --> 00:30:34,740
They became best buddies overnight.
This is great. I love it.

528
00:30:36,810 --> 00:30:38,540
Your daughter-in-law is...

529
00:30:39,540 --> 00:30:41,980
a very big-hearted person.

530
00:30:42,950 --> 00:30:43,950
Yes, she is.

531
00:30:44,310 --> 00:30:46,880
I really don't feel like
I deserve such good fortune,

532
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:48,990
but I was blessed
with a wonderful daughter-in-law.

533
00:30:51,150 --> 00:30:52,460
I stopped by because...

534
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:56,260
I wanted to ask
if you'd like to come over...

535
00:30:56,590 --> 00:30:58,230
to our place on Sunday,
if you're free.

536
00:30:59,260 --> 00:31:00,260
Pardon?

537
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:05,770
People at the market still gossip
about our families, you know.

538
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:08,570
With the show coming up,
I thought...

539
00:31:08,670 --> 00:31:11,210
it'd be a good chance
to quell the rumors.

540
00:31:13,240 --> 00:31:15,350
What do you say?

541
00:31:15,410 --> 00:31:19,050
- If you're too uncomfortable...
- No, not at all.

542
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:22,890
That sounds wonderful.
I'd love to. I'll be there.

543
00:31:22,990 --> 00:31:24,250
Oh, great.

544
00:31:24,590 --> 00:31:26,420
Then, it's been a while,

545
00:31:26,490 --> 00:31:29,960
but I think I'll make you
my steamed sea bream.

546
00:31:30,460 --> 00:31:33,460
The meat is still firm this season,
so it should be delicious.

547
00:31:34,500 --> 00:31:36,200
Your steamed sea bream?

548
00:31:37,830 --> 00:31:38,840
Yes.

549
00:31:40,870 --> 00:31:42,010
For real, Dad?

550
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:47,780
Of course, I'll be there.
But I already heard from Ms. Gong.

551
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:52,320
It's the pharmacist's birthday.
You know that, right?

552
00:31:55,390 --> 00:31:59,920
She wanted it kept secret.
But bring a substantial gift.

553
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:04,690
Something worthy of your wealth.
Got it?

554
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:09,230
Really? It's Ms. Na's birthday?

555
00:32:09,730 --> 00:32:12,200
Yes. When I was on the phone
with Hyun Bin earlier,

556
00:32:12,270 --> 00:32:13,570
he mentioned it was her birthday.

557
00:32:14,100 --> 00:32:17,270
Gosh, I think I used to celebrate it
back in the day,

558
00:32:17,740 --> 00:32:19,240
but I'd completely forgotten
about it.

559
00:32:20,210 --> 00:32:21,340
You didn't know either,
did you, Dad?

560
00:32:21,740 --> 00:32:24,310
I guess not.
My mind was on the sea bream.

561
00:32:25,420 --> 00:32:27,350
Is the steamed sea bream
really that delicious?

562
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:31,390
The steamed sea bream is one thing,
but her spicy pork's something else.

563
00:32:31,650 --> 00:32:35,260
Of course, yours is delicious too.
It's just a little different.

564
00:32:35,730 --> 00:32:37,430
I'll have to learn
her recipe this time.

565
00:32:38,530 --> 00:32:43,330
Man. What should I get her?
It's so hard to decide.

566
00:32:44,330 --> 00:32:46,540
Mom and I don't have to go, do we?

567
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:49,770
That's right.

568
00:32:50,070 --> 00:32:53,380
- We'll just stay home.
- But...

569
00:32:53,940 --> 00:32:57,150
Yes, it would be awkward
for you and Ji Hu to go there.

570
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:01,350
Ji Hu, while I'm gone,

571
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:03,750
you must be excited
to order some takeout.

572
00:33:03,950 --> 00:33:06,660
Yes. Mom, let's get malatang.

573
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:08,360
Sure.

574
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:14,060
(Yang Dong Suk)

575
00:33:16,900 --> 00:33:19,240
Is she really never going
to talk to me again?

576
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:23,240
Everyone else is getting along now,
but for us, it's just more awkward.

577
00:33:37,890 --> 00:33:40,060
All right,
the downstairs bathroom is clean!

578
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:42,660
I finished the upstairs bathroom
a while ago too.

579
00:33:42,730 --> 00:33:45,430
But what's he doing in his room?
Don't tell me he's asleep.

580
00:33:45,700 --> 00:33:48,500
Honey, who's sleeping?

581
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:52,140
Oh, are you volunteering
at the pediatric ward today?

582
00:33:52,140 --> 00:33:53,370
What? No.

583
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:57,370
- Then why the guitar?
- I have something to take care of.

584
00:33:57,940 --> 00:33:59,080
I'm heading out.

585
00:34:00,380 --> 00:34:02,010
What's he up to this time?

586
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:06,580
Is Dad practicing to sing
on that TV show?

587
00:34:06,920 --> 00:34:09,250
Then why not just practice at home
with our uncle?

588
00:34:10,620 --> 00:34:11,990
Where is he going?

589
00:34:12,890 --> 00:34:16,160
Dae Han.
There are two big tables in storage.

590
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:17,990
Bring them out
and wipe them down, please.

591
00:34:18,390 --> 00:34:19,400
Okay.

592
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:27,140
Where do you think you're going?
You didn't even clean.

593
00:34:28,910 --> 00:34:30,740
I did clean!
Can't you see how clean it is?

594
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:37,410
Look! See? This, here. Look!

595
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:41,950
Who's going to look under the bed?
As long as what's visible is clean.

596
00:34:42,390 --> 00:34:45,920
Seriously, the way you do things...
You're just like Dad.

597
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:48,320
I'm not that bad!

598
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:57,900
Seriously, what is wrong with him?

599
00:34:58,300 --> 00:35:00,000
When is he ever going to
break this habit?

600
00:35:03,370 --> 00:35:05,370
I can't take it. I just can't.

601
00:35:05,580 --> 00:35:09,750
Are Dad's socks under the bed again?
Hey, seriously, what is his problem?

602
00:35:10,250 --> 00:35:12,780
That's an incurable disease.
He'll never change.

603
00:35:12,850 --> 00:35:15,420
I guess it's a hereditary condition.
My sister's the same way.

604
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:17,320
Will you stop trying
to make me look bad?

605
00:35:18,420 --> 00:35:19,760
I'm heading out.

606
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:22,430
You were supposed to get groceries.
Where are you going?

607
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:26,330
How can she be so much
like her father?

608
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:29,600
I'll go with Grandma.
Uncle, you're coming with us, right?

609
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:32,840
Of course.
I even made a shopping list.

610
00:35:33,370 --> 00:35:37,710
- They're siblings, but different.
- Tell me about it.

611
00:35:47,580 --> 00:35:49,250
Guess what freesia stands for.

612
00:35:50,590 --> 00:35:51,620
A new beginning.

613
00:35:52,590 --> 00:35:54,920
- You looked it up!
- Of course, I did.

614
00:35:55,120 --> 00:35:58,090
It's your grandma's favorite,
so I had to know.

615
00:35:58,430 --> 00:36:01,300
They say it's a flower that blooms
when winter ends and spring arrives.

616
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,870
Doesn't that sound just like us?

617
00:36:03,170 --> 00:36:04,830
The cold air between our families...

618
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:07,270
is turning into
a warm spring breeze.

619
00:36:07,700 --> 00:36:08,700
You're right.

620
00:36:09,210 --> 00:36:11,570
My family is so happy.

621
00:36:12,010 --> 00:36:15,280
For your grandmother to be the one
who reached out first...

622
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:16,610
I can't tell you how thankful I am.

623
00:36:17,150 --> 00:36:21,750
No, it was your mother
who helped me first.

624
00:36:24,420 --> 00:36:25,420
So, what now?

625
00:36:26,020 --> 00:36:28,490
So, for our first home...
How about near the office?

626
00:36:29,490 --> 00:36:30,490
Come on.

627
00:36:31,630 --> 00:36:33,430
I wouldn't mind a quiet place
in the suburbs.

628
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:37,030
Then how about a house with a yard?
So our kids can run around.

629
00:36:37,100 --> 00:36:40,400
Let's name our kids using a syllable
from each of our names.

630
00:36:40,670 --> 00:36:43,640
- Like Ju Hyun and Ah Bin?
- I love it!

631
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:47,910
Should we just tell everyone
tomorrow that we're dating?

632
00:36:48,710 --> 00:36:51,310
No, let's wait.
Tomorrow is all about Grandma.

633
00:36:51,510 --> 00:36:52,520
You think so?

634
00:36:53,150 --> 00:36:54,580
Okay, we'll wait.

635
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:59,390
- We got everything for the japchae.
- Yes.

636
00:36:59,390 --> 00:37:00,690
Mom, wild chives.

637
00:37:00,860 --> 00:37:02,060
For the steamed sea bream?

638
00:37:02,690 --> 00:37:03,690
Oh, right.

639
00:37:03,990 --> 00:37:06,860
I should make
the spicy pork Dr. Yang loves.

640
00:37:06,860 --> 00:37:07,930
What?

641
00:37:08,860 --> 00:37:11,070
- Isn't that Dad and Dr. Yang?
- Yes.

642
00:37:11,070 --> 00:37:12,970
- You've still got it.
- Yes, I know.

643
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:15,200
- Mom!
- Are you getting groceries?

644
00:37:15,270 --> 00:37:16,270
Yes.

645
00:37:16,740 --> 00:37:20,280
But you said you were busy.
You meant meeting up with him?

646
00:37:20,540 --> 00:37:23,850
Yes. We were training for the show.

647
00:37:24,180 --> 00:37:25,720
And we practiced the song...

648
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,680
- we'll sing together on the show.
- Yes.

649
00:37:27,750 --> 00:37:28,750
Hold on a second.

650
00:37:29,250 --> 00:37:31,420
Hey, why do your faces look
so squeaky clean?

651
00:37:31,950 --> 00:37:34,090
And what's with the banana milk?

652
00:37:35,020 --> 00:37:36,190
Did you two just come
from the bathhouse?

653
00:37:36,430 --> 00:37:39,960
- The sauna is great after a hike.
- It's the best.

654
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:41,600
It's been a while since we scrubbed
each other's backs.

655
00:37:43,470 --> 00:37:47,200
- Okay, rest up. See you tomorrow.
- See you tomorrow.

656
00:37:47,970 --> 00:37:50,470
I'll see you tomorrow, Ms...
I mean, Mother.

657
00:37:51,710 --> 00:37:55,040
That takes me back.

658
00:37:55,540 --> 00:37:58,350
Please, Mother, don't be so formal.
It feels like you're being distant.

659
00:37:58,350 --> 00:37:59,750
He's right, Mom. Come on.

660
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:03,720
All right. Don't be late tomorrow.

661
00:38:03,820 --> 00:38:05,350
I won't! Thank you. Bye.

662
00:38:07,190 --> 00:38:09,360
Here, I got this specially for you.
It's all yours.

663
00:38:13,130 --> 00:38:15,830
Why did you buy so much? Wow.

664
00:38:15,930 --> 00:38:18,270
- I'm not done shopping yet.
- Okay. Oh, my.

665
00:38:21,070 --> 00:38:24,310
Auntie, I thought you weren't going.
Are you buying a gift?

666
00:38:24,940 --> 00:38:26,710
I can't be the only one
not to give her a gift.

667
00:38:26,910 --> 00:38:29,450
Then you can buy my gift too.

668
00:38:29,450 --> 00:38:31,880
If Grandpa or Dad
gives me my startup money,

669
00:38:31,950 --> 00:38:35,520
- you can take a cut of the profits.
- That's too complicated.

670
00:38:36,620 --> 00:38:38,520
Just how much do you need anyway?

671
00:38:39,090 --> 00:38:40,960
About twice what I have now?

672
00:38:41,690 --> 00:38:44,230
I'll take YouTube classes on
how to get a million subscribers...

673
00:38:44,230 --> 00:38:46,060
and get 1-on-1 coaching
from experts.

674
00:38:46,860 --> 00:38:49,030
I guess you've really
thought this through.

675
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:52,200
Of course. I want to be a woman
who's worthy of Woo Jae.

676
00:38:52,300 --> 00:38:55,440
Hey. Even if
our two families reconcile,

677
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:59,180
your mom and Dr. Han Seong Mi
will never become in-laws.

678
00:38:59,740 --> 00:39:03,810
Auntie, I'd just be happy
to date Woo Jae first, you know?

679
00:39:04,110 --> 00:39:08,080
How about this? It's light and comfy
for her workouts.

680
00:39:08,550 --> 00:39:11,550
- It's a very popular gift.
- Really?

681
00:39:11,550 --> 00:39:14,360
- Yes.
- Then I'll take this one for now.

682
00:39:15,060 --> 00:39:18,960
Then could I see some shoes or a hat
that would go with this outfit?

683
00:39:19,030 --> 00:39:20,660
Of course. Right this way.

684
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:30,240
Auntie, this hat... Hello.

685
00:39:30,810 --> 00:39:32,240
Oh, hi.

686
00:39:48,260 --> 00:39:50,130
Just ring it up with your things.

687
00:39:50,390 --> 00:39:51,590
- Okay.
- I'm heading out.

688
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:52,960
Okay, Auntie.

689
00:39:53,630 --> 00:39:54,700
Dong Suk.

690
00:39:57,630 --> 00:40:01,400
Try to understand. It's awkward
when you two see each other.

691
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:11,750
- Right, honey.
- Yes?

692
00:40:12,250 --> 00:40:14,720
Do you realize you almost slipped up
in front of Hyun Bin yesterday?

693
00:40:15,180 --> 00:40:16,820
- I did?
- Yes.

694
00:40:16,820 --> 00:40:20,090
You almost said
we posted that video.

695
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:21,520
Really?

696
00:40:21,820 --> 00:40:23,560
You have to be really careful
tomorrow.

697
00:40:23,660 --> 00:40:26,600
If that family finds out,
we'll be right back at square one.

698
00:40:26,700 --> 00:40:27,900
I'll keep that in mind, honey.

699
00:40:28,500 --> 00:40:32,740
- I'd better not drink at all.
- Right, don't.

700
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:38,510
- This bed's surprisingly plush.
- Yes, isn't it?

701
00:40:38,870 --> 00:40:40,910
Give it a proper try.

702
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:44,680
Come to the middle,
where the acupressure feature is.

703
00:40:44,980 --> 00:40:46,020
That feels good.

704
00:40:47,020 --> 00:40:50,520
Its acupressure and massage features
are popular with homemakers.

705
00:40:50,950 --> 00:40:53,320
That feels amazing.

706
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:55,290
I feel all my tension
melting away, honey.

707
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,730
It's pretty amazing, right?

708
00:40:57,030 --> 00:40:59,830
You should have just accepted it
when Hyun Bin offered to buy it.

709
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:02,460
Maybe I should have.
This feels so good.

710
00:41:02,930 --> 00:41:04,700
I think the pharmacist
would really love this.

711
00:41:05,840 --> 00:41:08,200
- Thank you. Have a good day.
- You too. Thanks.

712
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:12,980
All right, let's earmark this one
and check out what you saw.

713
00:41:13,310 --> 00:41:15,180
Okay, we still have a little time.

714
00:41:15,580 --> 00:41:16,880
Wait, why this?

715
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:21,220
After your sister opens her shop,
I'm thinking of opening one myself.

716
00:41:21,550 --> 00:41:24,990
I'll get a retail manager's license
to open my own store.

717
00:41:25,150 --> 00:41:28,190
That would suit you perfectly.
You could sell anything, Cha Se Ri.

718
00:41:29,690 --> 00:41:32,390
But is Dong Suk making any progress
with her store?

719
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,430
Yes, it seems like
she's been looking at storefronts.

720
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:36,530
- With her boyfriend.
- Really?

721
00:41:36,530 --> 00:41:38,330
- Yes.
- Already?

722
00:41:38,770 --> 00:41:41,100
Who's this guy?
Tell her to bring him over sometime.

723
00:41:44,170 --> 00:41:46,380
(Top-Tier, High-Profit
Delivery Franchise!)

724
00:41:49,550 --> 00:41:51,350
I've looked at so many,
but I still have no idea.

725
00:41:52,010 --> 00:41:54,250
Who am I kidding,
thinking I could run a business?

726
00:41:56,890 --> 00:41:57,990
(Gong Dae Han)

727
00:42:10,570 --> 00:42:12,370
What is it now?

728
00:42:14,040 --> 00:42:15,340
Meet me at the teahouse
in the market.

729
00:42:15,740 --> 00:42:16,940
I'll only wait for one hour.

730
00:42:17,670 --> 00:42:19,140
If you're not here in an hour,

731
00:42:20,380 --> 00:42:21,540
I'm barging into your house.

732
00:42:23,380 --> 00:42:25,080
What? He's going to barge in?

733
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:30,590
Welcome.

734
00:42:37,290 --> 00:42:38,290
You're here.

735
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:45,500
Thanks for coming.

736
00:42:47,070 --> 00:42:48,400
What did you want to see me about?

737
00:42:49,270 --> 00:42:50,270
Right.

738
00:42:51,310 --> 00:42:52,310
Here.

739
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:55,310
It's a list of restaurants
that might work for you. And...

740
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:59,420
I put together some notes
on what's needed to open a place.

741
00:43:00,420 --> 00:43:02,580
You didn't have to do all this.

742
00:43:02,850 --> 00:43:03,890
Also,

743
00:43:04,890 --> 00:43:07,220
the restaurant
where we almost kissed...

744
00:43:07,220 --> 00:43:08,320
My gosh!

745
00:43:09,160 --> 00:43:10,160
Keep your voice down.

746
00:43:10,790 --> 00:43:11,790
Right, sorry.

747
00:43:12,830 --> 00:43:15,800
Anyway, about that place,
the owner put it up for sale.

748
00:43:16,530 --> 00:43:19,640
- Really?
- Yes, Woo Jae works there.

749
00:43:20,200 --> 00:43:24,640
As you know, it's a good size.
Perfect for you to run on your own.

750
00:43:25,010 --> 00:43:27,140
Right. Thank you.

751
00:43:31,510 --> 00:43:32,580
Hey, Dong Suk.

752
00:43:33,550 --> 00:43:35,080
You're still coming to my place
tomorrow, right?

753
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:37,920
No.

754
00:43:38,850 --> 00:43:42,620
If I go, it'll just be
a painful reminder of who's gone.

755
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:46,200
It's your mother's birthday.
They should only be happy, right?

756
00:43:46,630 --> 00:43:49,160
I know, but it's not right for you
to be the only one not there.

757
00:43:50,070 --> 00:43:51,400
Ji Hu's dad...

758
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:55,470
told Ji Hu what happened
at the courthouse.

759
00:43:58,870 --> 00:44:01,110
- He did?
- Ji Hu...

760
00:44:01,480 --> 00:44:04,510
doesn't want me
spending time with you.

761
00:44:05,750 --> 00:44:08,980
Right, I can see
why he'd feel that way.

762
00:44:10,950 --> 00:44:13,190
When I told you
not to contact me again,

763
00:44:14,420 --> 00:44:17,430
I wasn't just saying that
because I was angry.

764
00:44:18,230 --> 00:44:20,600
No matter how much things improve
between our families,

765
00:44:22,970 --> 00:44:26,440
we need to keep our distance.

766
00:44:31,010 --> 00:44:32,410
I should get going.

767
00:44:32,910 --> 00:44:35,440
And thank you for this. Really.

768
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:58,230
Father!
Your outfit is fantastic today.

769
00:44:58,430 --> 00:45:01,040
I love the hat.
You should wear it all the time.

770
00:45:02,440 --> 00:45:03,440
Father.

771
00:45:04,310 --> 00:45:05,810
Why are you so tense?

772
00:45:06,340 --> 00:45:08,940
I couldn't sleep, thinking
about that steamed sea bream.

773
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,880
Honey, isn't it about time we left?

774
00:45:13,050 --> 00:45:15,050
I know,
but what's taking her so long?

775
00:45:15,780 --> 00:45:18,190
Yang Eun Bin,
we're leaving without you!

776
00:45:18,990 --> 00:45:20,590
Wait, I'm ready!

777
00:45:21,160 --> 00:45:22,830
Wow, all dressed up.
Are you going on a blind date?

778
00:45:23,160 --> 00:45:25,190
This is even more important.

779
00:45:26,230 --> 00:45:29,870
While we're away, go have fun
on a date with your boyfriend.

780
00:45:30,070 --> 00:45:33,870
- What? I don't have one.
- Yes, you do.

781
00:45:34,170 --> 00:45:36,770
That guy from the neighborhood
you went to a motel with.

782
00:45:37,510 --> 00:45:39,910
Hey. How did you know
about the motel?

783
00:45:40,140 --> 00:45:42,710
How do you think I know?
Someone must've told me.

784
00:45:43,180 --> 00:45:45,610
- Don't tell Ji Hu about this, okay?
- Mom.

785
00:45:45,750 --> 00:45:46,750
You scared me!

786
00:45:47,550 --> 00:45:48,550
What are you keeping secret from me?

787
00:45:51,150 --> 00:45:53,090
Well... You caught me.

788
00:45:53,560 --> 00:45:57,130
I was going to order
sweet and sour pork with malatang.

789
00:45:57,190 --> 00:45:59,330
I wanted to surprise you.
You know what I mean, sweetie?

790
00:46:04,930 --> 00:46:06,340
- Here?
- Yes.

791
00:46:06,340 --> 00:46:07,570
Oh, my. Mom.

792
00:46:08,070 --> 00:46:12,240
Why so much food?
The table legs will break.

793
00:46:12,370 --> 00:46:14,580
- Right, Dae Han?
- You could say that.

794
00:46:14,810 --> 00:46:18,610
Seriously? Once their whole family
gets here and sits down,

795
00:46:18,810 --> 00:46:21,220
it's going to be completely packed.
Right, Mom?

796
00:46:21,580 --> 00:46:23,190
It sure will be. It's been a while.

797
00:46:24,820 --> 00:46:26,290
Is this everything?

798
00:46:26,590 --> 00:46:27,660
This looks delicious,
and so does this.

799
00:46:27,720 --> 00:46:29,320
Mom, is the soup ready yet?

800
00:46:35,030 --> 00:46:36,030
Is it not good?

801
00:46:36,300 --> 00:46:37,300
"Not good?"

802
00:46:38,270 --> 00:46:39,800
It's a disaster.

803
00:46:39,970 --> 00:46:43,340
- Did you follow a recipe?
- I looked at one.

804
00:46:43,440 --> 00:46:46,880
Wow, Mom.
Good thing you focused on studies.

805
00:46:47,480 --> 00:46:48,680
Hush.

806
00:46:49,410 --> 00:46:52,750
What should I do? Add something?
Salt? Some kind of seasoning?

807
00:46:52,880 --> 00:46:55,580
Don't add anything.
It already tastes like a stew.

808
00:46:55,650 --> 00:46:56,650
Add water. Just water.

809
00:46:56,990 --> 00:47:00,160
Gosh, they'll be here any minute.
This is a disaster.

810
00:47:03,490 --> 00:47:07,000
So this is my future.

811
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:10,800
- No, that won't happen.
- Mom.

812
00:47:10,870 --> 00:47:11,870
Just be quiet.

813
00:47:15,170 --> 00:47:16,640
It's been a while,
hasn't it, Grandfather?

814
00:47:17,710 --> 00:47:18,710
Back in the day,

815
00:47:19,170 --> 00:47:21,280
I'd come and go
like I owned the place.

816
00:47:21,980 --> 00:47:22,980
To think that I,

817
00:47:23,980 --> 00:47:25,150
before I die,

818
00:47:26,450 --> 00:47:28,780
get to see this house again.

819
00:47:34,460 --> 00:47:36,730
(148 Suyang-ro)

820
00:47:38,260 --> 00:47:40,030
- You're here.
- Welcome.

821
00:47:40,100 --> 00:47:42,730
- Welcome.
- Thank you for having us, Doctor.

822
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,700
- Jeong Han, we're here.
- Hey.

823
00:47:44,770 --> 00:47:48,200
- Ma'am, my father is here as well.
- Please, come in.

824
00:47:48,900 --> 00:47:50,770
Happy birthday.

825
00:47:51,340 --> 00:47:53,480
- Oh, my.
- Happy birthday, Ms. Na.

826
00:47:53,480 --> 00:47:56,310
Oh, dear.
I asked everyone not to mention it.

827
00:47:56,680 --> 00:47:58,980
- Honestly.
- It's my fault.

828
00:47:58,980 --> 00:48:00,620
I told Director Yang.

829
00:48:00,980 --> 00:48:05,590
Good job, sweetie.
Mom, the more the merrier.

830
00:48:05,590 --> 00:48:06,820
- Stop it. My goodness.
- Come on.

831
00:48:07,820 --> 00:48:10,790
Oh, my goodness. Dr. Han,
did you make all this yourself?

832
00:48:11,090 --> 00:48:12,390
No, not at all.

833
00:48:13,060 --> 00:48:14,330
I only made the seaweed soup.

834
00:48:14,900 --> 00:48:18,230
- Please, have a seat.
- Yes, let's sit down.

835
00:48:18,530 --> 00:48:20,170
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

836
00:48:20,240 --> 00:48:22,340
- Eun Bin, make sure you eat plenty.
- Thank you.

837
00:48:23,310 --> 00:48:25,970
- This is seasoned perfectly.
- Grandma, this is so delicious.

838
00:48:26,780 --> 00:48:29,240
- The pork is so good.
- Is it?

839
00:48:29,310 --> 00:48:30,850
Grandma, this is so good. Seriously.

840
00:48:31,510 --> 00:48:33,150
- This is amazing.
- Eat up.

841
00:48:33,250 --> 00:48:34,520
- Mom, this is seasoned perfectly.
- Is it?

842
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:36,250
- Yes.
- It's so good.

843
00:48:39,090 --> 00:48:40,760
- Try this too.
- Is it good?

844
00:48:43,830 --> 00:48:46,030
Maybe have something other
than the seaweed soup.

845
00:48:47,700 --> 00:48:51,330
No, it's fine. I'm done.
I'm watching my figure,

846
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:53,300
so I don't eat very much
to begin with.

847
00:48:54,670 --> 00:48:58,870
How is it?
Does it taste like you remember?

848
00:48:59,270 --> 00:49:03,080
Yes.
It's a taste I've missed dearly.

849
00:49:04,510 --> 00:49:05,510
I'm so glad.

850
00:49:06,250 --> 00:49:08,380
He was so excited
for your steamed sea bream...

851
00:49:08,380 --> 00:49:09,990
he couldn't sleep a wink.

852
00:49:12,390 --> 00:49:15,160
It's been a while since you've had
my mom's spicy pork, hasn't it?

853
00:49:15,820 --> 00:49:16,830
Jeong Han.

854
00:49:17,830 --> 00:49:19,660
This is so strange.

855
00:49:20,260 --> 00:49:21,630
The food tastes so good,

856
00:49:22,700 --> 00:49:24,800
- but why am I tearing up?
- Oh, man.

857
00:49:26,100 --> 00:49:29,440
Seong Mi. No, Dr. Han Seong Mi.

858
00:49:30,840 --> 00:49:32,470
What kind of tears are these,
exactly?

859
00:49:32,970 --> 00:49:36,310
It's the recall of emotional memory
triggered by a gustatory stimulus.

860
00:49:36,610 --> 00:49:37,680
The Proust effect.

861
00:49:38,780 --> 00:49:42,080
My, that's so impressive.
It's like if someone just taps you,

862
00:49:42,150 --> 00:49:44,150
all these brilliant words
just come pouring out, Doctor.

863
00:49:46,390 --> 00:49:50,290
This is so heartwarming.
What a beautiful day.

864
00:49:55,760 --> 00:49:59,900
I know this wasn't an easy decision,
so thank you for inviting us.

865
00:49:59,970 --> 00:50:00,970
Well...

866
00:50:01,270 --> 00:50:04,540
I can't really take the credit
for this gathering.

867
00:50:04,910 --> 00:50:07,940
This is all thanks to Ms. Cha.

868
00:50:08,580 --> 00:50:10,650
She was the first
to offer her generous support,

869
00:50:11,180 --> 00:50:13,350
which is what gave me
the courage to do this.

870
00:50:14,150 --> 00:50:15,780
Thank you so much.

871
00:50:16,550 --> 00:50:20,560
I'd like to take this opportunity
to thank you as well.

872
00:50:21,020 --> 00:50:23,330
My goodness, no. It was nothing.

873
00:50:25,090 --> 00:50:29,160
Both our families will be
on "Human Theater" together,

874
00:50:29,660 --> 00:50:31,300
but the people at the market
think that we...

875
00:50:31,570 --> 00:50:33,540
are still mortal enemies.

876
00:50:34,470 --> 00:50:36,840
So with this opportunity,
let's put the bad blood behind us,

877
00:50:37,270 --> 00:50:39,370
and I hope we can get along
from now on.

878
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:42,980
Enough talk, let's eat.
It's so good I can't even hear you.

879
00:50:43,150 --> 00:50:44,950
Right, go on. Dig in.

880
00:50:46,350 --> 00:50:48,280
- This is delicious.
- It really is.

881
00:50:48,320 --> 00:50:49,320
Please, eat.

882
00:50:49,680 --> 00:50:50,690
Please, you too.

883
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:53,320
Eat up, Hyun Bin.

884
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:57,760
This is delicious.
You have some too, okay?

885
00:50:58,890 --> 00:51:00,260
Hyun Bin, try the sea bream.

886
00:51:00,330 --> 00:51:02,060
Yes, Father. Please, eat.

887
00:51:06,330 --> 00:51:07,470
One, two, three!

888
00:51:08,070 --> 00:51:11,810
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>

889
00:51:12,110 --> 00:51:15,780
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>

890
00:51:16,110 --> 00:51:20,320
<i>- Happy birthday, dear Mom</i>
<i>- Happy birthday, dear Grandma</i>

891
00:51:20,620 --> 00:51:24,690
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>

892
00:51:25,820 --> 00:51:27,120
Happy birthday, Ms. Na.

893
00:51:29,190 --> 00:51:30,260
Oh, my!

894
00:51:30,730 --> 00:51:31,730
Happy birthday.

895
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:34,160
Thank you.

896
00:51:35,160 --> 00:51:38,130
This is Gongjindan.
I made it myself.

897
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:42,140
It will help with your circulation
and boost your vitality.

898
00:51:42,640 --> 00:51:44,310
Be sure to chew it well
on an empty stomach.

899
00:51:44,510 --> 00:51:47,310
This is too much. I don't know
if I should accept this.

900
00:51:47,640 --> 00:51:48,840
Thank you so much.

901
00:51:49,880 --> 00:51:50,880
Thank you so much.

902
00:51:51,550 --> 00:51:53,150
Well, Ms. Na.

903
00:51:53,650 --> 00:51:55,050
- Honey.
- Me?

904
00:51:55,580 --> 00:51:56,820
Yes. This is for you.

905
00:51:59,490 --> 00:52:01,560
It's a solid gold key.

906
00:52:03,930 --> 00:52:07,460
It symbolizes our families uniting
and opening a new door together.

907
00:52:09,300 --> 00:52:10,300
Thank you.

908
00:52:10,970 --> 00:52:12,930
You really go all out, don't you?

909
00:52:13,640 --> 00:52:16,840
My aunt and I
picked this out for you.

910
00:52:16,970 --> 00:52:18,070
- Oh, my.
- Nice.

911
00:52:18,310 --> 00:52:21,210
- Thank you. I'll love wearing it.
- Great.

912
00:52:21,640 --> 00:52:24,310
It's too bad
Dong Suk couldn't be here.

913
00:52:25,480 --> 00:52:29,020
I miss her a lot.
I can't help but worry about her.

914
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:31,520
- I know.
- Don't you worry.

915
00:52:31,790 --> 00:52:34,320
Dong Suk is already seeing someone.

916
00:52:34,690 --> 00:52:36,530
- Really?
- Goodness, honey.

917
00:52:36,890 --> 00:52:40,000
It's a secret for now, Father.
Please pretend you didn't hear that.

918
00:52:40,300 --> 00:52:43,500
Except it's a secret
we all already know.

919
00:52:43,570 --> 00:52:45,970
Wow, Aunt Dong Suk sure moves fast.

920
00:52:46,700 --> 00:52:50,310
Hey, I met her right after
my divorce too, you know.

921
00:52:50,570 --> 00:52:52,510
Wow, Dad, listen to you bragging.

922
00:52:55,480 --> 00:52:58,580
So, please,
don't worry about Dong Suk.

923
00:52:59,150 --> 00:53:02,720
And I hope you find someone
special soon too, Mr. Gong.

924
00:53:02,920 --> 00:53:04,420
- Thanks.
- That would be nice.

925
00:53:04,820 --> 00:53:07,420
I'm sure Dae Han will find
someone great soon.

926
00:53:08,620 --> 00:53:12,330
All right, then. It's my turn
to give you your gift, Mom.

927
00:53:12,730 --> 00:53:13,730
Here we go.

928
00:53:14,130 --> 00:53:16,300
What's this? Dad,
did you write another song?

929
00:53:16,970 --> 00:53:20,770
- Goodness. There's no stopping him.
- You wrote a song for me?

930
00:53:21,070 --> 00:53:24,570
Yes. We wrote it just for you, Mom.

931
00:53:24,640 --> 00:53:26,780
"We?" Did you write the song
with Uncle?

932
00:53:27,180 --> 00:53:28,180
It wasn't me.

933
00:53:35,280 --> 00:53:36,690
Three, four.

934
00:53:37,590 --> 00:53:41,520
<i>On our different paths in life</i>

935
00:53:42,690 --> 00:53:47,330
<i>We've wandered for far too long</i>

936
00:53:49,200 --> 00:53:54,370
<i>Never knowing our hearts were closed</i>

937
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:59,270
<i>All we did was resent each other</i>

938
00:54:00,580 --> 00:54:05,980
<i>Today is the day</i>
<i>we become a family again</i>

939
00:54:06,380 --> 00:54:12,020
<i>A precious day, though long overdue</i>

940
00:54:14,660 --> 00:54:19,890
<i>- Let's all hold hands</i>
<i>- Let's all hold hands</i>

941
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:22,860
<i>- Let our house</i>
<i>- Let our house</i>

942
00:54:22,860 --> 00:54:25,700
<i>- Be filled with laughter</i>
<i>- Be filled with laughter</i>

943
00:54:25,930 --> 00:54:31,340
<i>- Today, we become a family again</i>
<i>- Today, we become a family again</i>

944
00:54:31,570 --> 00:54:34,380
<i>- From now on</i>
<i>- From now on</i>

945
00:54:34,410 --> 00:54:39,950
<i>- Let's live our lives with love</i>
<i>- Let's live our lives with love</i>

946
00:54:42,150 --> 00:54:44,450
Happy birthday.
"Let's live our lives with love."

947
00:54:53,400 --> 00:54:55,100
I've gotten so old,

948
00:54:56,830 --> 00:54:59,070
but this house hasn't changed a bit.

949
00:55:00,770 --> 00:55:04,370
I tried to hold back the years
with all sorts of repairs...

950
00:55:05,110 --> 00:55:06,810
and touch-ups.

951
00:55:09,510 --> 00:55:10,510
Over there.

952
00:55:11,550 --> 00:55:13,650
We used to put a big basin there
and fill it with water,

953
00:55:14,250 --> 00:55:15,750
then the kids
would splash around in it.

954
00:55:16,750 --> 00:55:18,590
We washed cabbage
and made kimchi there too.

955
00:55:21,520 --> 00:55:22,790
The kids' father...

956
00:55:24,190 --> 00:55:26,030
I wonder if he ever
misses those days.

957
00:55:27,460 --> 00:55:29,030
I'm not sure about their father,

958
00:55:31,630 --> 00:55:35,640
but I'm sure my kids' mother
doesn't miss it at all.

959
00:55:37,110 --> 00:55:38,440
You, on the other hand,

960
00:55:39,270 --> 00:55:42,280
have lived a blameless life.

961
00:55:43,040 --> 00:55:44,050
But me...

962
00:55:44,750 --> 00:55:47,420
In Ok, the mother of my children...

963
00:55:48,220 --> 00:55:50,120
I wronged her terribly.

964
00:55:51,420 --> 00:55:54,290
I wish I could see her
just one more time before I die.

965
00:55:55,020 --> 00:55:57,290
There's something
I desperately need to tell her.

966
00:56:03,160 --> 00:56:04,400
Being this happy
for the first time in a while...

967
00:56:05,230 --> 00:56:07,140
It's making me think of her
that much more.

968
00:56:08,370 --> 00:56:12,410
I have a lot on my mind today too.

969
00:56:17,680 --> 00:56:19,080
Hey.

970
00:56:19,650 --> 00:56:22,920
You can't just barge
into a private space like this.

971
00:56:23,590 --> 00:56:27,620
I wasn't even pulling.
You followed me up here on your own.

972
00:56:28,060 --> 00:56:31,030
Eun Bin?
Maybe we shouldn't be up here.

973
00:56:31,090 --> 00:56:34,960
Why, Ju Ah? When you're a guest,
a tour is part of the deal.

974
00:56:35,460 --> 00:56:37,130
No, it's just...

975
00:56:38,500 --> 00:56:39,600
So, where's your room, Woo Jae?

976
00:56:40,400 --> 00:56:41,400
Behind you.

977
00:56:41,770 --> 00:56:42,770
Sweet!

978
00:56:45,810 --> 00:56:48,380
It's perfect
for our honeymoon suite.

979
00:56:49,040 --> 00:56:51,110
Come on in. Let's try out the bed.

980
00:56:51,180 --> 00:56:52,650
Hey! What do you mean,
"try out the bed?"

981
00:56:53,010 --> 00:56:54,020
Hey!

982
00:56:55,380 --> 00:56:56,650
I can't believe I'm finally here.

983
00:56:57,250 --> 00:56:58,390
Show me your room too.

984
00:56:58,690 --> 00:57:01,220
- No way.
- Why not? Show me.

985
00:57:01,460 --> 00:57:02,860
I said no.

986
00:57:03,120 --> 00:57:05,760
It's a lady's room. You can't enter
without my parents' permission.

987
00:57:06,730 --> 00:57:08,700
And yet, you waltz in and out
of my apartment whenever you want.

988
00:57:09,130 --> 00:57:10,370
That's different.

989
00:57:10,530 --> 00:57:14,470
Why not? I want to see the pajamas
with the stretched-out neck.

990
00:57:14,670 --> 00:57:16,300
You were eavesdropping
on my call with my dad.

991
00:57:16,570 --> 00:57:19,910
Not eavesdropping. You didn't
hang up, so I heard everything.

992
00:57:20,540 --> 00:57:24,010
- I'm going in.
- I said no! Absolutely not!

993
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:26,450
All right, I'm going in.

994
00:57:35,420 --> 00:57:36,620
What are you looking at?

995
00:57:37,830 --> 00:57:42,000
I can tell our doctor here
has never had to lift a finger.

996
00:57:43,160 --> 00:57:44,170
I suppose it's obvious.

997
00:57:44,730 --> 00:57:47,640
Let me just handle all this.
You should rest.

998
00:57:51,070 --> 00:57:54,110
A mother-in-law like Ms. Na
is a rare find.

999
00:57:54,410 --> 00:57:57,310
You should teach Ms. Gong housework
before she gets married.

1000
00:57:57,380 --> 00:57:58,750
It'll save her an earful
from her in-laws.

1001
00:57:59,950 --> 00:58:01,550
My Ju Ah is a great cook.

1002
00:58:01,920 --> 00:58:03,720
She's good at anything she does
with her hands.

1003
00:58:04,450 --> 00:58:07,090
Is that so? That's a relief.

1004
00:58:07,560 --> 00:58:11,490
But she has found someone to marry,
so what's there to worry about?

1005
00:58:11,560 --> 00:58:12,830
My Hyun Bin is the one
I have to worry about.

1006
00:58:14,060 --> 00:58:16,230
You saw me, right?
Totally barking up the wrong tree.

1007
00:58:17,430 --> 00:58:20,030
But you know...

1008
00:58:20,670 --> 00:58:23,100
This might be a little forward
of me to say, but...

1009
00:58:23,710 --> 00:58:27,280
To be honest, when I first saw
the VP and Director Yang,

1010
00:58:28,040 --> 00:58:29,340
I actually thought
they were a couple.

1011
00:58:29,980 --> 00:58:31,750
My gosh, you did?

1012
00:58:32,010 --> 00:58:35,180
Yes. When the VP
was praising Director Yang,

1013
00:58:35,380 --> 00:58:37,420
her eyes were just full of hearts.

1014
00:58:38,650 --> 00:58:39,690
My goodness.

1015
00:58:39,690 --> 00:58:42,860
Apparently, there are rumors at work
that they're a couple.

1016
00:58:43,790 --> 00:58:44,860
Goodness, are you serious?

1017
00:58:45,630 --> 00:58:49,100
And you're sure Director Yang
isn't seeing anyone, right?

1018
00:58:50,200 --> 00:58:53,070
It seems like there is someone
he's interested in.

1019
00:58:54,340 --> 00:58:56,240
Then maybe...

1020
00:58:56,440 --> 00:58:59,440
one of them is more into it
than the other?

1021
00:59:00,780 --> 00:59:02,280
My gosh, Doctor.

1022
00:59:02,540 --> 00:59:04,550
So, does that mean
I can get my hopes up?

1023
00:59:05,550 --> 00:59:07,280
I shouldn't have said anything.

1024
00:59:08,220 --> 00:59:11,720
Not at all.
Doctor, you've been a huge help.

1025
00:59:12,550 --> 00:59:13,720
By the way...

1026
00:59:14,090 --> 00:59:16,490
I've started studying,
thanks to you, Doctor.

1027
00:59:17,430 --> 00:59:19,460
That's wonderful news.

1028
00:59:20,300 --> 00:59:23,360
I'll have you over to my place
next time. You have to come.

1029
00:59:24,000 --> 00:59:25,100
I'd love that.

1030
00:59:25,870 --> 00:59:28,970
About what happened with Ju Ah...
Thank you again.

1031
00:59:30,170 --> 00:59:33,840
To be honest, at first I thought
you had staged the whole thing.

1032
00:59:33,910 --> 00:59:35,240
What? Oh, my.

1033
00:59:36,880 --> 00:59:38,010
Goodness, Doctor.

1034
00:59:38,580 --> 00:59:40,880
I'm really not that kind of person.

1035
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,890
I'm sorry.
I completely misunderstood.

1036
00:59:44,520 --> 00:59:46,250
I sincerely apologize.

1037
00:59:47,090 --> 00:59:48,090
It's okay.

1038
00:59:51,130 --> 00:59:52,130
You don't have to walk us out.

1039
00:59:52,560 --> 00:59:53,800
- Wait.
- We'll be on our way now.

1040
00:59:53,860 --> 00:59:55,730
But there's more food.
You should stay longer.

1041
00:59:55,730 --> 00:59:57,630
- No, really. I ate way too much.
- Oh, come on.

1042
00:59:57,700 --> 00:59:59,200
- You're full too, right, Dad?
- Did you have enough to eat?

1043
00:59:59,270 --> 01:00:01,200
I need to go on a diet. Hey, you...

1044
01:00:01,270 --> 01:00:04,170
- The meal was wonderful. Thank you.
- Not at all.

1045
01:00:04,170 --> 01:00:05,910
- Thank you.
- Thank you for the meal.

1046
01:00:05,970 --> 01:00:07,410
- Thank you for everything today.
- Of course.

1047
01:00:07,410 --> 01:00:08,610
My dear husband.

1048
01:00:08,910 --> 01:00:10,950
- Exactly.
- For the 1st time in 30 years,

1049
01:00:11,010 --> 01:00:13,720
- Right? It's a shame.
- we had special guests over.

1050
01:00:13,820 --> 01:00:15,350
- Hey, you're right.
- Hey, let's go sing some karaoke!

1051
01:00:15,420 --> 01:00:17,990
I scrubbed every nook and cranny
of the house clean,

1052
01:00:18,720 --> 01:00:20,560
shopped until my hands were full,

1053
01:00:20,560 --> 01:00:23,260
- Get home safe.
- and finally, we all gathered.

1054
01:00:23,290 --> 01:00:25,260
- Go on inside, Mother.
- With a fluttering heart,

1055
01:00:25,730 --> 01:00:28,760
we shared
a truly joyful meal together.

1056
01:00:31,600 --> 01:00:33,770
The years I spent filled
with hatred and resentment...

1057
01:00:34,370 --> 01:00:36,070
now feel like such a waste.

1058
01:00:37,010 --> 01:00:40,110
I guess time truly does
make you forget many things.

1059
01:00:46,080 --> 01:00:48,180
Now, my only remaining wish...

1060
01:00:49,880 --> 01:00:54,290
is to forget even the last shred
of longing I have for you.

1061
01:00:56,620 --> 01:01:00,760
To forget that in the end,
you never returned.

1062
01:01:04,100 --> 01:01:05,130
And so now,

1063
01:01:05,700 --> 01:01:08,500
I'll pull out the large nail
that is you,

1064
01:01:09,440 --> 01:01:12,110
the one lodged deep in my heart,
causing me pain.

1065
01:01:13,810 --> 01:01:15,240
And I'll fill that empty space...

1066
01:01:15,910 --> 01:01:19,780
with the happy laughter and warmth
of our two families.

1067
01:01:21,350 --> 01:01:24,990
I plan to live the rest of my days
loving a little more.

1068
01:01:38,730 --> 01:01:40,770
Today, I'm meeting
the "Human Theater" producer...

1069
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:42,470
to sign the contract.

1070
01:01:43,240 --> 01:01:47,680
Congratulations, honey.
It took a while, but we did it.

1071
01:01:48,380 --> 01:01:51,750
This is all thanks to you.

1072
01:01:53,050 --> 01:01:54,280
But listen, honey,

1073
01:01:54,680 --> 01:01:57,350
you really can't slip up
in front of Dr. Gong.

1074
01:01:57,790 --> 01:01:59,920
Yesterday, you won't believe
what Dr. Han Seong Mi said to me.

1075
01:02:00,460 --> 01:02:02,160
She thought I faked the whole thing.
Can you believe it?

1076
01:02:02,660 --> 01:02:04,530
- Really?
- Yes.

1077
01:02:04,930 --> 01:02:06,460
I could barely keep a straight face.

1078
01:02:07,460 --> 01:02:08,800
She's sharp.

1079
01:02:09,600 --> 01:02:11,470
That's Han Seong Mi for you.

1080
01:02:12,200 --> 01:02:14,570
But soaring high above
the great Han Seong Mi...

1081
01:02:14,640 --> 01:02:18,170
is my phoenix, Cha Se Ri.

1082
01:02:21,280 --> 01:02:22,280
You look dashing.

1083
01:02:32,490 --> 01:02:34,660
Let's see here.

1084
01:02:36,660 --> 01:02:39,560
I see a bond in your son's life
that goes back many years.

1085
01:02:40,060 --> 01:02:41,430
My gosh, you're right.

1086
01:02:41,730 --> 01:02:44,670
There's a woman he's known
for a very long time.

1087
01:02:46,670 --> 01:02:48,300
As the years have turned,

1088
01:02:48,700 --> 01:02:50,340
the thread of their bond
has grown loose.

1089
01:02:50,710 --> 01:02:51,810
Then we must tie it.

1090
01:02:52,110 --> 01:02:55,340
How can I bind them together
so tightly?

1091
01:02:55,780 --> 01:02:57,080
It must be bound by written words.

1092
01:02:57,450 --> 01:03:01,720
With a talisman powerful enough
to startle the spirits.

1093
01:03:05,550 --> 01:03:06,750
Yes, I understand.

1094
01:03:07,690 --> 01:03:08,690
Thank you.

1095
01:03:10,590 --> 01:03:11,590
Wait.

1096
01:03:12,590 --> 01:03:14,960
Why do I hear the cry of a newborn?

1097
01:03:17,470 --> 01:03:18,470
What?

1098
01:03:19,900 --> 01:03:23,570
Even if you rip it out by the roots,
it will always claw its way back.

1099
01:03:24,110 --> 01:03:25,210
The bond with a child.

1100
01:03:26,410 --> 01:03:28,910
- What?
- Because you raise another child,

1101
01:03:29,280 --> 01:03:31,010
you think
you'll escape punishment...

1102
01:03:31,010 --> 01:03:32,580
for leaving
your own flesh and blood?

1103
01:03:34,950 --> 01:03:36,150
A bond you have abandoned...

1104
01:03:36,650 --> 01:03:39,650
will always return
to exact its price.

1105
01:03:40,290 --> 01:03:41,290
Mark my words.

1106
01:05:00,000 --> 01:05:02,970
(Recipe For Love)

1107
01:05:03,070 --> 01:05:06,470
There's been a crime.
We're in pursuit of the suspect.

1108
01:05:06,540 --> 01:05:08,910
- What kind of punk did this?
- You scared me!

1109
01:05:08,910 --> 01:05:12,680
I made some ginseng chicken soup,
and I was worried it would spoil.

1110
01:05:14,280 --> 01:05:16,550
By the way, what's that?
Why is it wrapped up so tightly?

1111
01:05:16,620 --> 01:05:18,990
This is just a soap set
I got for the holidays.

1112
01:05:19,120 --> 01:05:20,690
That's some fancy wrapping
for just a soap set.

1113
01:05:21,820 --> 01:05:22,820
Goodbye.

1114
01:05:24,030 --> 01:05:25,430
Want to go on a blind date?

1115
01:05:25,830 --> 01:05:28,700
Even Dong Suk is seeing someone now,
you know.

1116
01:05:29,560 --> 01:05:31,330
- You like it, right?
- Of course, I do.

1117
01:05:31,330 --> 01:05:33,100
I look forward
to getting to know you.
